CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 21, 1945, pg. 15 reads: "Bride And Groom - A pair of happy newlyweds, Corp. and Mrs. Carl Morris, were snapped just about to cut the wedding cake last Thursday at their reception at the home of the bride's father on Wylie Avenue. The lovely bride is the former Eloise Mosby.  The groom is stationed at Tampa, Fla. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Carl Morris, groom wearing military uniform, and Eloise Mosby, bride wearing dress with bow and covered buttons down bodice, cutting three tiered cake in interior surrounded by group of men and women
